│                                                                                            │
│ The fix is to make the `canReuseExtract` check in                                          │
│ `llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp` more robust by preventing the reuse of   │
│ an extract from a PHI node if the user is in a different basic block.                      │
│                                                                                            │
│ **File:** `llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp`                                │
│ **Lines to add at line 2913:**                                                             │
│ ```cpp                                                                                     │
│   // It is not safe to reuse the extract if the operand is a PHI                           │
│   // and the extract is in a different block.                                              │
│   if (isa<PHINode>(Op) && I->getParent() != cast<Instruction>(Op)->getParent())            │
│     return false;                                                                          │
│ ```                                                                                        │
│ This code should be inserted after the existing `isa<PHINode>(I)` check.                   │
│                                                                                            │
│ ### 5. Conclusion                                                                          │
│                                                                                            │
│ The `SIGABRT` is caused by the SLP vectorizer generating invalid LLVM IR, which is then    │
│ caught by the verifier pass. The root cause is an overly aggressive optimization in        │
│ `BoUpSLP::canReuseExtract` that incorrectly allows the reuse of a value from a PHI node    │
│ across basic blocks within a loop. This leads to an SSA violation.                         │
│                                                                                            │
│ The proposed fix makes the check more conservative by disallowing this specific unsafe     │
│ reuse. This prevents the incorrect code motion and ensures that the generated IR remains   │
│ valid, thus fixing the crash.                                                              │
│ --------------------  END  --------------------                                            │
